    {
        "id": "eb117bba353d71f7",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "d216577e3e3a3883",
        "name": "easy-pid-controller v2.0.0 — anti-windup, output clamp, deadband, bumpless transfer, runtime gains, reset",
        "info": "Updated for simple-pid-controller v2.0.0.\n\nNew input topics (via MQTT or inject):\n  pid/gains        → { k_p, k_i, k_d } — runtime gain tuning\n  pid/mode         → 'auto' or 'manual' — bumpless transfer on manual→auto\n  pid/manual_output → number — manual output seed\n  reset            → any — clears integral, derivative, timestamp\n\nOutput payload now includes: error, output (raw clamped), mode\nInfluxDB: pid_status measurement stores all fields with mode as tag.",
        "x": 500,
        "y": 60,
        "wires": []
